---
/**
 * domain-agent-design 0001 · Figure 4 — "Blast radius decides where the gate goes".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/domain-agent-design/lessons/0001-the-domain-agent-design-method.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup id="r6b">). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the same reason as Fig1. This figure references no
 * arrowhead markers, so it needs no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A blast-radius ladder: read-only actions auto-allow, bounded writes auto-allow under a threshold, and irreversible or fan-out actions pause for a human approval gate."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Blast radius decides where the gate goes</text
        >

        <!-- ladder rows -->
        <rect x="40" y="40" width="560" height="34" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="56" y="61" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >read order / account / KB</text
        >
        <text x="584" y="61" text-anchor="end" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >&#10003; auto-allow &mdash; zero blast radius</text
        >

        <rect x="40" y="82" width="560" height="34" rx="6" fill="#fdf3e7" stroke="#c2700f"></rect>
        <text x="56" y="103" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#c2700f"
            >issue refund &le; $50</text
        >
        <text x="584" y="103" text-anchor="end" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#c2700f"
            >&#10003; auto-allow under a bounded cap</text
        >

        <rect x="40" y="124" width="560" height="34" rx="6" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="56" y="145" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >refund &gt; $50 &middot; close account &middot; escalate to billing</text
        >
        <text x="584" y="145" text-anchor="end" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >&#9888; gate &mdash; pause for a human</text
        >

        <rect
            x="40"
            y="166"
            width="560"
            height="34"
            rx="6"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
        <text x="56" y="187" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >delete / bulk action across many records</text
        >
        <text x="584" y="187" text-anchor="end" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >&#9888; gate &mdash; irreversible &amp; fan-out</text
        >

        <text
            x="320"
            y="224"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#9a2417"
            >The valve between "agent proposed" and "system did" &mdash; placed where blast radius
            exceeds trusted autonomy.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="242" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >More unsupervised reach &rarr; the gate matters more, not less.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        An <b>approval gate</b> is the valve between "agent proposed" and "system did."<sup
            ><a href="#s5" id="r6b">6</a></sup
        > Gate by <em>action</em>, not globally: auto-allow the zero-blast reads, cap the cheap
        writes, and pause the irreversible or fan-out actions for a human. Sizing the blast radius
        of each action is what tells you where the gate belongs.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
